  "text": "The mean length of time taken to input the data into the FaHRAS system does require time which would result in longer consultation times. The mean time to complete a risk assessment was 3.9 minutes over the whole study. This ranged from a mean time of 4.7 minutes for the first hundred patients to 3.1 minutes for the final 100 patients. The FaHRAS programme compares favorably to other computer based programmes which can take up to 15 minutes to input all the relevant data [CITATION_1] . If computer based programs are used it enables pedigrees to be generated and for family history information to be stored. FaHRAS is therefore ideal in a well resourced breast system and could be completed by trained breast nurses.",
